Rates are high for the fast-growing economy, as the discovery of huge shelf gas and coal reserves in the northwest could attract more than $50 billion as investments in the next few years from companies such as Rio Tinto, Vale from Brazil, Eni from Italy and Anadarko from the United States.
The ruling Frelimo party, the leading political force since 1975, and the Renamo party accuse each other of the tensions.
