Everything is subsidized in Germany: from coal to cars and farmers.
Everything but the IT industry.
Nevertheless, the scope and technical advancements of the U.S. spy agencies, which became famous through Snowden’s revelations, were a shock to some companies who previously thought the greatest risk of surveillance was China.
A big shift is taking place in cloud technologies, where executives of European companies are better aware that data stored in the U.S. is in the same jurisdiction and therefore potentially vulnerable.
