FAA: "Air passengers can now use gadgets on planes (but not call from mobile phones)"
Passengers will be able to use their electronic devices throughout the flight to read, work, play games, watch movies and listen to music, but not talk on mobile phones, according to the long-awaited new guidelines released on Thursday by the Federal Aviation Administration.
