Among the most popular materials in the last five months are notes about the helplessness of the Kremlin in relations with Ukraine, the death of the soloist of the group "King and the joke", pogroms in the capital Biryulev.
Rosbalt's conflict with Roskomnadzor began in July 2013 when amendments to the media law, which prohibited journalists from blasphemy, came into force.
The agency found a prohibited vocabulary in two videos published on the agency’s website (“Gigit of Krasnodar” and “Pussy Riot defiled oil towers”).
The other parties describe differently.
Roskomnadzor on the basis of the detected videos accused Rosbalt of gross and systematic violation of the media law and appealed to the court with the demand to take away the license from the agency.
